The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	Mumbai, June 25 (PTI): Model Viveka Babaji was today found dead inside her apartment in suburban Bandra, with police saying it could be a case of suicide.          
	Babajis body was found hanging from a ceiling fan at her residence. She was 37.          
	Viveka, a former Miss World contestant, had appeared in Kamasutra, Coca-Cola and Live In Jeans ads. She had also acted in a film called Yeh Kaisi Mohabbat, co-starring Sharad Kapoor and Deepak Tijori. The film bombed at the box office.           
	Viveka was born and brought up in Mauritius. She was crowned Miss Mauritius in 1993.                   
	New Delhi: The railways have decided to make special arrangements for the physically challenged in all mail and express trains. Doors of coaches are being widened to facilitate the boarding of passengers with wheel-chairs. Besides, a handicapped quota of two sleeper-class berths  one lower berth for the physically challenged person and the middle berth for an escort  will be provided.                   New Delhi (PTI): Telecom operator MTNL has signed an agreement with JNU to provide 3G and WiFi  high-speed Internet access  on the campus. Students will be able to access the Internet for Rs 199 a month.                                                                                                                                              
